author_ssm: Daniel Callahan and Sam Markham, September 2004 - June 2005.
unittitle_ssm: German Correspondence from the World Wars Collection
abstract_ssm: German Correspondence from the World Wars contains letters to/from German soldiers and their friends and family. Only one set of correspondence, that of soldier Hermann Lappan, is from the First World War. The collection also contains two diaries of a German soldier involved in the Balkan Campaign, miscellaneous soldiers' documents, as well as correspondence (in English) between a young Italian soldier and a young American student.
subject_ssm: World War, 1939-1945 -- United States -- Public opinion.
title_ssm: We lay aside letters never to read them again, and at last we destroy them out of discretion, and so disappears the most beautiful, the most immediate breath of life, irrecoverable for ourselves and for others.
Frontsoldaten: the German soldier in World War II
Das andere Gesicht des Krieges: Deutsche Feldpostbriefe, 1939-1945
"Ich will raus aus diesem Wahnsinn": deutsche Briefe von der Ostfront 1941-1945: aus sowjetischen Archiven
Kriegsalltag: Die Rekonstruktion des Kreigsalltags als Aufgabe der historischen Forschung und der Friedenserziehung
Lebenszeichen 1945: Feldpost aus den letzten Kriegstagen
Der Krieg des Kleinen Mannes: Eine Militärgeschichte von unten
